OL,6,F"The areas in which the ECB has failed
OL,7,Fto meet the ambition of the ICEC are
OL,8,Foften those in which commercial
OL,9,Fconsiderations still appear to have
OL,10,Ftrumped the moral imperative for
OL,11,Faction, such as on equal pay and on
OL,12,Ftalent pathway costs.
OL,14,F"While much of the game has supported
OL,15,Fthe work of the ICEC and the ECB has
OL,16,Fbegun to implement its work, there
OL,17,Fremains the ability to sanction those
OL,18,Fwho fail to meet the standards
OL,19,Frequired."
